<title>USA: VASCO  arranges $2.5 million bridge loan.</title>
<headline>VASCO  arranges $2.5 million bridge loan.</headline>
<dateline>LOMBARD, Ill. 1997-07-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Vasco Corp said Tuesday it arranged a $2.5 million bridge loan with Generale Bank NV of Brussels.</p>
<p>The loan is a convertible note with an annual interest rate of 3.25 percent and can be converted into Vasco stock at a discount based on the timing of a secondary stock offering, Vasco said.</p>
<p>Generale Bank has had a long banking relationship with Digipass SA, a Belgian-based company that Vasco acquired last year, the company said.</p>
